					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10041816#post-4128547</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10041816/scp-3739#post-4128547</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 23 Jan 2019 19:09:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Lt Flops</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1735419</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The pained cries of our bovine Mother kept us awake through the night. We asked her, <em>what is the cure to mortality? What is a life of freedom beyond the nourishing teat, betwixt the folds of your rotund figure?</em> We know not the answer. We know only to pour our inequities back into that tarn from which we first emerged. And those beyond the enrichment of her inked Udder meet those depths with a prod. Branded with empty affectation. Never to grasp what they were destined for.</p> <p>Our few words, let lactate across these lorn lines, are but a measly outpouring. We will not let whey lay waste. And neither will you. Will you join us? Or will you mewl like missing cattle, cast off into the fleeting dark?</p> <p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">also i think you're going to regret that</span></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10041816#post-4128536</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10041816/scp-3739#post-4128536</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 23 Jan 2019 18:58:15 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>4980602</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a feeding frenzy of ADHD brilliance. There are some parts of this that are so out-there that they feel <em>years</em> ahead of their time. The creativity is off the charts. I appreciate the omnipresent thematic fidelity to cows; MTF names, operation names, and all the subtleties in there I can't recount.</p> <p>I feel like the whole thing is a great central core concept that was injected with a maximum dose of epinephrine and then slapped on the rear. It's beating a million miles a minute and honestly gets more difficult to read and process as it progresses, edging a little towards exhausting (in no small part due to the pace and complexity of the concepts presented, so that could be too much of a good thing). I guess what I'm saying is that some more restraint with respect to the directions taken would have suited the article a bit, imo.</p> <p>Having said that, have my awed +1 as you accelerate on by (+3 since starting to read) and be expecting me to pop in for some re-reads.</p> <p>And that new pataphysics logo is too cool.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
